    Scope and Contents
Clark, teacher, discusses early to mid 20th century rural life along the Mississippi River: growing up and living in Grand Tower, Illinois; her family and their experiences on the river; her father Captain E.L. Poe; riverboats and their pilots; the Depression; one room schools and college education; teaching; homemade foods and remedies; joining the WAC's during WWII; the treatment of African Americans; and sex discrimination.3 tapes, 174 mins., 44 pp.
Interview by Kevin Corley, 1984 
